snippet.textDisplay: I liked that despite dissing the blue box you actually didn't dismiss the blue box, you showed that it was stupidly delicious by scarfing it down while you threw out those stereotypical complaints, then exhibited a desire to emulate it's smooth texture by defiantly following through with the powdered cheese approach, yes you could argue that was the challenge, but I've seen so many people just instantly abandon it and go straight to making oven baked mac and cheese.
